# Animably — Project Overview

Viral motion-graphics platform. Users browse video templates, customize them with a
brand kit, preview live with Remotion, and export MP4/WebM/MOV (incl. alpha).

## Monorepo layout (npm workspaces, Node >=20)

- `apps/web` — Next.js 15 (App Router) + React 19 app. The product.
- `apps/render-worker` — Hono server that renders Remotion compositions server-side
  (ProRes 4444 / H.264). Imports directly from `apps/web/src/lib` and `template-sdk`.
- `packages/template-sdk` — shared template/overlay catalog + TS types. No build step;
  consumed via `@video-lib/template-sdk` source.
- `packages/database` — Drizzle ORM schema + Neon Postgres client (`@video-lib/database`).

## Stack

- Next.js 15 App Router, React 19, TypeScript (strict).
- Tailwind CSS v4 (`@tailwindcss/postcss`), `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` via `cn()` in `lib/utils`.
- Remotion 4 for compositions, live preview (`@remotion/player`), and rendering.
- Clerk auth (`@clerk/nextjs`), Stripe billing, Drizzle + Neon, Vercel Blob for storage.

## Conventions

- Use the `@/*` path alias for imports inside `apps/web` (maps to `apps/web/src`).
- Every external integration is **gated by env presence** so the app runs locally with
  nothing configured. Mirror this: check `isAuthEnabled()`, `isClerkConfigured()`,
  `isDatabaseConfigured()`, `isServerExportEnabled()` before using a service, and degrade
  gracefully (return `null`/`[]`/fallback) instead of throwing.
- Prefer editing the shared `template-sdk` catalog/types over duplicating template data.

## Commands

- `npm run dev` (web, port 3000), `npm run dev:worker` (render worker).
- `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, `npm run db:push`.
